  "text": "The Java ClassLoader delegation chain in OpenJDK implements a hierarchical class loading architecture that follows the parent-first delegation model. Here are the key components:\n\n1. **java/lang/ClassLoader.java (src/java.base/share/classes/java/lang/ClassLoader.java)**: Contains the foundational ClassLoader class with the protected method loadClass(String name, boolean resolve) at line 534. This method implements the parent-first delegation strategy by first checking if a class is already loaded, then delegating to the parent class loader if available, and finally calling findClass() to locate the class.\n\n2. **jdk/internal/loader/BuiltinClassLoader.java (src/java.base/share/classes/jdk/internal/loader/BuiltinClassLoader.java)**: Extends SecureClassLoader and serves as the base class for the three built-in class loaders (boot, platform, and application). Its loadClassOrNull(String cn, boolean resolve) method at line 589 implements a specialized delegation model for modules: it first checks if a package is in a module defined to the loader, delegates to the appropriate loader, and then checks the parent class loader or the class path.\n\n3. **jdk/internal/loader/ClassLoaders.java (src/java.base/share/classes/jdk/internal/loader/ClassLoaders.java)**: Defines the three built-in class loaders:\n   - BootClassLoader (line 131): Handles bootstrap module loading\n   - PlatformClassLoader (line 146): Loads platform modules\n   - AppClassLoader (line 161): Loads application classes\n   These are instantiated in the static initializer block (line 63) and are accessible via bootLoader(), platformClassLoader(), and appClassLoader() methods.\n\n4. **src/hotspot/share/classfile/classLoader.cpp**: The HotSpot C++ implementation that provides native support for class loading operations, including interaction with the module system and class path resolution.\n\n5. **src/hotspot/share/classfile/systemDictionary.hpp and systemDictionary.cpp**: The SystemDictionary class manages the cache of all loaded classes organized by ClassLoaderData. Key methods include:\n   - resolve_or_fail(Symbol* class_name, Handle class_loader, bool throw_error, TRAPS): Loads a class and throws an error if not found\n   - resolve_or_null(Symbol* class_name, Handle class_loader, TRAPS): Loads a class and returns null if not found\n   These methods are the core of the HotSpot class loading mechanism, tracking classes in per-ClassLoaderData dictionaries.\n\nThe delegation chain flows from Java's public ClassLoader.loadClass() through the protected internal methods, ultimately reaching the HotSpot SystemDictionary which maintains the global cache of loaded classes and enforces thread-safety through the SystemDictionary_lock."
